benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve bundle audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request: Happy path returns 200 with application/json and array of AuditLog objects; schema asserted and bundleId consistency checked (TC01).
Empty Response: Bundle with no audit logs returns 200 with empty array (TC02).
Error for Non-Existing Resource: 404 when bundleId not found (TC03, TC15, TC16).
Input Validation: Invalid UUID and special-character/whitespace bundleIds handled with 400/404 (TC04, TC19, TC20) and UUID boundary case covered (TC09).
Query Parameters: Unexpected query parameter does not break endpoint and still returns 200 (TC08).
Authorization: Missing and invalid tokens return 401 (TC05, TC06).
Content Negotiation/Headers: Content-Type application/json asserted on success (TC01, TC02).
Resilience/Availability: Service unavailable 503 covered (TC07) and transient failure with retry (TC12).
Performance/Load: Large dataset performance and concurrent requests covered (TC10, TC17).
HTTP Method Enforcement: Non-GET request yields 405 (TC21).
Security Hardening: SQL injection attempt safely handled without leaking internals (TC11).
Behavioral Consistency: Alignment with other audit log endpoints checked (TC14).
Regression robustness: Known malformed entries no longer reproduced (TC13).
gaps: Pagination: No scenarios validating pagination behavior for large result sets (e.g., limit/offset, next links) if supported by this endpoint.
Query Parameters breadth: Only an unexpected param is tested; no coverage for any documented/allowed query params or explicit rejection if none are allowed.
Authorization depth: No coverage for 403 Forbidden (e.g., authenticated but not authorized/insufficient permissions).
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No scenarios for burst traffic receiving 429 or appropriate headers.
Caching Behavior: No checks for ETag/If-None-Match, Last-Modified/If-Modified-Since, or Cache-Control headers and 304 Not Modified flow.
Error Response Contract: For 404/400/503, no validation of standardized error schema/headers (content-type, error code fields).
Content-Type on errors: Only success responses assert application/json; error responses lack content-type assertions.
recommendations: Add pagination scenarios: verify presence/behavior of limit/offset or cursor parameters, correct page sizes, stable ordering, and navigation links; confirm behavior when parameters are omitted or out of range.
Expand query parameter coverage: if the API supports none, add a scenario asserting 400 for any unexpected params; if it supports some, test valid and invalid combinations.
Add authorization scenario for 403 Forbidden: authenticated user lacking scope/role attempting access.
Introduce rate limiting tests: send bursts to trigger 429, verify Retry-After header, and system recovery after cooldown.
Add caching tests: capture ETag/Last-Modified on first 200; reissue request with If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since to assert 304 and header correctness; verify Cache-Control semantics.
Validate standardized error payloads and headers for 400/404/503: assert content-type, error codes/messages fields match API error spec.
Assert Content-Type on error responses consistently (application/json) to ensure clients can parse error bodies.
